<quiz>
  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Comparing earthquake magnitudes using logarithms</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>
The magnitude of an earthquake is measured using a logarithmic scale. An earthquake of magnitude {@m2@} and another of magnitude {@m1@} are recorded.
</p>

<p>
Find how many times more powerful the larger earthquake is compared to the smaller one.
</p>

<p>
[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]
</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
The difference in magnitude is:
</p>

<p>
\[
{@m2@} - {@m1@} = {@diff@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Each increase of 1 in magnitude means 10 times more intensity.
</p>

<p>
So the ratio is:
</p>

<p>
\[
10^{@diff@}
\]
</p>

<p>
\[
= {@ratio@}
\]
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
